{
  "doc_id": "14178",
  "text": "In a review of the basic science of autoimmune pancreatitis, Park et al. [CITATION_1] discuss animal models and human studies of AIP, highlighting the potential role of cellular immunity [CITATION_2] , the complement system [CITATION_3] , molecular mimickry [CITATION_4] and regulatory T-cells [CITATION_5] . Based on this, they have proposed a plausible model for the pathogenesis of AIP that includes an explanation of both Types 1 and 2 AIP.",
